Once you do it, it takes
away fear 90% of the time.

00:12:04.170 --> 00:12:06.140 align:middle line:90%
The other thing that we do--

00:12:06.140 --> 00:12:08.143 align:middle line:84%
nobody fears a
wonderful teacher.

00:12:08.143 --> 00:12:10.310 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if you think back
to your high school years,

00:12:10.310 --> 00:12:12.470 align:middle line:84%
or college years,
even grade school,

00:12:12.470 --> 00:12:14.900 align:middle line:84%
we all had at least one
teacher that was really good.

00:12:14.900 --> 00:12:17.180 align:middle line:90%
And we didn't fear that teacher.

00:12:17.180 --> 00:12:19.100 align:middle line:84%
The key of getting
over fear of failure

00:12:19.100 --> 00:12:21.140 align:middle line:84%
is learning how
to make failure--

00:12:21.140 --> 00:12:23.360 align:middle line:90%
your past failures-- a teacher.

00:12:23.360 --> 00:12:25.460 align:middle line:84%
So what we do is, we
have people revisit some

00:12:25.460 --> 00:12:27.260 align:middle line:90%
of their most hurtful failures.

00:12:27.260 --> 00:12:29.600 align:middle line:84%
With me, I had a
failed first marriage.

00:12:29.600 --> 00:12:32.150 align:middle line:84%
And as I was getting
ready to get married

00:12:32.150 --> 00:12:34.477 align:middle line:84%
for the second time,
eight years ago,

00:12:34.477 --> 00:12:36.810 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to make sure I didn't
repeat the same mistakes.

00:12:36.810 --> 00:12:38.120 align:middle line:90%
So I revisited that marriage.

00:12:38.120 --> 00:12:40.620 align:middle line:84%
I looked at all of
the reasons it failed.

00:12:40.620 --> 00:12:43.130 align:middle line:84%
And then I applied those
reasons to the new marriage

00:12:43.130 --> 00:12:44.182 align:middle line:90%
that was about to happen.

00:12:44.182 --> 00:12:45.140 align:middle line:90%
I said, OK, I did this.

00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:45.530 align:middle line:90%
I did that.

00:12:45.530 --> 00:12:46.340 align:middle line:90%
I did that.

00:12:46.340 --> 00:12:48.170 align:middle line:90%
Now, I don't want to repeat it.

00:12:48.170 --> 00:12:50.210 align:middle line:90%
Failure became a teacher.

00:12:50.210 --> 00:12:52.430 align:middle line:84%
The more we do that with
some of our major failures

00:12:52.430 --> 00:12:54.590 align:middle line:84%
that we've had in life,
then all of a sudden,

00:12:54.590 --> 00:12:57.860 align:middle line:84%
it becomes a teacher rather
than a dreaded enemy.

00:12:57.860 --> 00:12:59.810 align:middle line:90%
And then we no longer fear it.

00:12:59.810 --> 00:13:03.440 align:middle line:84%
And failure, as it turns out, is
one of the most critical steps

00:13:03.440 --> 00:13:05.610 align:middle line:90%
to extraordinary success.

00:13:05.610 --> 00:13:08.105 align:middle line:84%
And one of the reasons that
Spielberg and Steve Scott,

00:13:08.105 --> 00:13:10.550 align:middle line:84%
and Lee Iacocca, and
some of the other--

00:13:10.550 --> 00:13:12.140 align:middle line:90%
Sam Walton, who created Walmart.

00:13:12.140 --> 00:13:14.780 align:middle line:84%
The reason we achieved
the kind of success

00:13:14.780 --> 00:13:16.430 align:middle line:84%
in pursuing our
dreams is because we

00:13:16.430 --> 00:13:17.900 align:middle line:84%
went through lots of
failures and learned

00:13:17.900 --> 00:13:18.810 align:middle line:90%
how to deal with it.

00:13:18.810 --> 00:13:20.060 align:middle line:84%
So that's just one
of the chains we have

00:13:20.060 --> 00:13:20.660 align:middle line:90%
to cut-- one of the six chains.

00:13:20.660 --> 00:13:23.420 align:middle line:84%
>> No, it's really true, because
I think most people do not

00:13:23.420 --> 00:13:25.080 align:middle line:90%
learn from their successes.

00:13:25.080 --> 00:13:25.880 align:middle line:10%
>> No.

00:13:25.880 --> 00:13:27.360 align:middle line:84%
Success teaches
you almost nothing.

00:13:27.360 --> 00:13:29.040 align:middle line:84%
It builds your
arrogance and pride,

00:13:29.040 --> 00:13:33.080 align:middle line:84%
and makes you almost
blind to truth, sometimes.

00:13:33.080 --> 00:13:35.270 align:middle line:10%
But failure, if
you won't run away

00:13:35.270 --> 00:13:36.620 align:middle line:10%
from it-- which most people do.

00:13:36.620 --> 00:13:37.210 align:middle line:90%
If you really--

00:13:37.210 --> 00:13:38.210 align:middle line:84%
>> Say, where is
the lesson here.

00:13:38.210 --> 00:13:38.795 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, exactly.

00:13:38.795 --> 00:13:39.320 align:middle line:90%
And write it down.

00:13:39.320 --> 00:13:40.550 align:middle line:90%
>> Why was this in my life?

00:13:40.550 --> 00:13:41.515 align:middle line:90%
>> Write it down.

00:13:41.515 --> 00:13:42.890 align:middle line:84%
And the people
that were involved

00:13:42.890 --> 00:13:44.420 align:middle line:84%
in that failure
with you oftentimes

00:13:44.420 --> 00:13:45.837 align:middle line:84%
will have insights
you don't have.

00:13:45.837 --> 00:13:48.173 align:middle line:84%
So you can't just say, OK,
why do I think it failed?

00:13:48.173 --> 00:13:50.090 align:middle line:84%
You go back to other
people that were involved

00:13:50.090 --> 00:13:51.590 align:middle line:84%
and say, why do
you think I failed?

00:13:51.590 --> 00:13:54.132 align:middle line:84%
And they'll come up with ideas
that you didn't even think of.

00:13:54.132 --> 00:13:55.280 align:middle line:90%
And you write those down.

00:13:55.280 --> 00:13:57.940 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
wisdom begins to build.

00:13:57.940 --> 00:14:00.780 align:middle line:84%
And that wisdom ensures
your success in the future,

00:14:00.780 --> 00:14:05.005 align:middle line:84%
and really counteracts the
possibility of future failure.

00:14:05.005 --> 00:14:06.380 align:middle line:84%
>> You say--
speaking of failure,

00:14:06.380 --> 00:14:08.580 align:middle line:84%
one of the things we hate
most in life is criticism.

00:14:08.580 --> 00:14:09.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:14:09.380 --> 00:14:10.760 align:middle line:84%
That's another
one of the chains.

00:14:10.760 --> 00:14:11.560 align:middle line:90%
>> And-- I know.

00:14:11.560 --> 00:14:13.500 align:middle line:90%
And you said, welcome it.

00:14:13.500 --> 00:14:14.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:14:14.300 --> 00:14:15.258 align:middle line:90%
But it's hard to do it.

00:14:15.258 --> 00:14:16.350 align:middle line:90%
It's one thing to say it.

00:14:16.350 --> 00:14:17.517 align:middle line:90%
It's another thing to do it.

00:14:17.517 --> 00:14:19.538 align:middle line:10%
Because criticism
always hurts, even--

00:14:19.538 --> 00:14:21.080 align:middle line:10%
I mentioned in the
book that it never

00:14:21.080 --> 00:14:24.290 align:middle line:10%
ceases to amaze me,
the power of mothers

00:14:24.290 --> 00:14:26.390 align:middle line:10%
over their adult
daughters, even.

00:14:26.390 --> 00:14:28.025 align:middle line:84%
They'll say a simple
criticism and it

00:14:28.025 --> 00:14:29.600 align:middle line:90%
will wipe the daughter out.

00:14:29.600 --> 00:14:33.170 align:middle line:84%
Well, we teach a technique that
takes the power of criticism

00:14:33.170 --> 00:14:34.933 align:middle line:90%
to hurt you away forever.

00:14:34.933 --> 00:14:36.350 align:middle line:84%
In fact, Stephen
Covey-- who wrote

00:14:36.350 --> 00:14:38.570 align:middle line:84%
"7 Habits of Highly
Successful People,"

00:14:38.570 --> 00:14:40.880 align:middle line:84%
when he endorsed the
book, he made the comment

00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:42.590 align:middle line:84%
that the insights
on criticism alone

00:14:42.590 --> 00:14:44.210 align:middle line:90%
made the book worth the read.

00:14:44.210 --> 00:14:46.220 align:middle line:84%
And we show you one
technique that, when

00:14:46.220 --> 00:14:49.310 align:middle line:84%
you begin to use that
technique, it not only

00:14:49.310 --> 00:14:51.740 align:middle line:84%
takes all the pain of
criticism away forever--

00:14:51.740 --> 00:14:54.110 align:middle line:84%
you never have to be
hurt by criticism again--

00:14:54.110 --> 00:14:57.620 align:middle line:84%
but it also shows you how to
mine that criticism for gold.

00:14:57.620 --> 00:14:59.420 align:middle line:84%
So instead of being
a dreaded enemy,

00:14:59.420 --> 00:15:01.880 align:middle line:90%
it becomes a real valued ally.

00:15:01.880 --> 00:15:03.800 align:middle line:84%
And it's a real
simple technique.

00:15:03.800 --> 00:15:06.320 align:middle line:84%
You can use it with
criticism from your spouse,

00:15:06.320 --> 00:15:08.000 align:middle line:84%
from your friends,
from your boss.

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:09.830 align:middle line:84%
Doesn't matter
where it comes from.

00:15:09.830 --> 00:15:11.420 align:middle line:84%
You can all of a
sudden turn criticism

00:15:11.420 --> 00:15:13.100 align:middle line:90%
into a wonderful friend.

00:15:13.100 --> 00:15:13.900 align:middle line:90%
>> So?

00:15:13.900 --> 00:15:14.180 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:15:14.180 --> 00:15:15.200 align:middle line:90%
What is that technique?

00:15:15.200 --> 00:15:18.270 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'll tell you a story
that I tell in the book.

00:15:18.270 --> 00:15:21.077 align:middle line:84%
A man and woman walked
into a pet shop one day,

00:15:21.077 --> 00:15:22.160 align:middle line:90%
and they were all excited.

00:15:22.160 --> 00:15:24.870 align:middle line:84%
It's Saturday morning, they were
going to go look for a new dog.

00:15:24.870 --> 00:15:27.200 align:middle line:84%
And as they walk
into the pet store,

00:15:27.200 --> 00:15:29.552 align:middle line:84%
there's a parrot
sitting on a perch.

00:15:29.552 --> 00:15:31.010 align:middle line:84%
And this parrot
goes, "Hey, buddy!"

00:15:31.010 --> 00:15:32.650 align:middle line:90%
The guy goes, "Yeah?"

00:15:32.650 --> 00:15:35.810 align:middle line:84%
And the parrot goes, "You're
stupid and your wife's ugly!"

00:15:35.810 --> 00:15:37.670 align:middle line:90%
And he goes, "Excuse me?"

00:15:37.670 --> 00:15:39.560 align:middle line:84%
I said, "You're stupid
and your wife's ugly!"

00:15:39.560 --> 00:15:41.350 align:middle line:84%
Well, the wife, she's
a little overweight.

00:15:41.350 --> 00:15:42.517 align:middle line:90%
She instantly starts crying.

00:15:42.517 --> 00:15:43.500 align:middle line:90%
The man's furious.

00:15:43.500 --> 00:15:46.342 align:middle line:84%
He finds the manager of
the store and he said,

00:15:46.342 --> 00:15:48.050 align:middle line:84%
I can't believe what
your bird just said.

00:15:48.050 --> 00:15:49.967 align:middle line:84%
He called my wife ugly
and he said I'm stupid.

00:15:49.967 --> 00:15:52.520 align:middle line:84%
And he goes, the manager says,
oh, did he do that again?

00:15:52.520 --> 00:15:53.502 align:middle line:90%
And he goes, yeah.

00:15:53.502 --> 00:15:55.460 align:middle line:84%
Well, the manager puts
on this big, long glove,

00:15:55.460 --> 00:15:57.380 align:middle line:90%
goes over, grabs the parrot.

00:15:57.380 --> 00:15:58.460 align:middle line:90%
Bam, bam, bam.

00:15:58.460 --> 00:16:00.577 align:middle line:90%
Just slaps it silly.

00:16:00.577 --> 00:16:02.660 align:middle line:84%
And the man and his wife
feel a little vindicated.

00:16:02.660 --> 00:16:05.480 align:middle line:84%
So they look around for
their dog and don't find it.

00:16:05.480 --> 00:16:07.850 align:middle line:84%
They started to walk
out of the door.

00:16:07.850 --> 00:16:10.520 align:middle line:84%
And on their way out, the
parrot goes, "Hey, buddy."

00:16:10.520 --> 00:16:11.960 align:middle line:90%
And the guy goes, "Yeah?"

00:16:11.960 --> 00:16:15.410 align:middle line:10%
He goes, "You know."

00:16:15.410 --> 00:16:17.110 align:middle line:90%
Now, the point of the story.

00:16:17.110 --> 00:16:19.023 align:middle line:84%
Well, the parrot was
smarter than the people.

00:16:19.023 --> 00:16:21.440 align:middle line:84%
You see, the parrot had given
them a criticism-- actually,

00:16:21.440 --> 00:16:22.970 align:middle line:90%
two criticisms.

00:16:22.970 --> 00:16:27.110 align:middle line:84%
And what they didn't do is,
they didn't respond correctly.

00:16:27.110 --> 00:16:30.303 align:middle line:84%
The first thing we teach
is, consider the source.

00:16:30.303 --> 00:16:31.970 align:middle line:84%
Now, in this case,
it was only a parrot.

00:16:31.970 --> 00:16:34.320 align:middle line:84%
What does a parrot know
about intelligence or beauty?

00:16:34.320 --> 00:16:34.830 align:middle line:90%
Nothing.

00:16:34.830 --> 00:16:35.630 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:16:35.630 --> 00:16:37.590 align:middle line:84%
So the criticism
was totally invalid.

00:16:37.590 --> 00:16:39.510 align:middle line:84%
We say, when you
consider the source,

00:16:39.510 --> 00:16:41.838 align:middle line:84%
you also consider
the motivation.

00:16:41.838 --> 00:16:43.380 align:middle line:84%
What's their expertise
or motivation?

00:16:43.380 --> 00:16:45.810 align:middle line:84%
When that former boss might--
even though he was a Harvard

00:16:45.810 --> 00:16:49.200 align:middle line:84%
MBA, even though he was a senior
vice president of marketing,

00:16:49.200 --> 00:16:52.560 align:middle line:84%
when he told me, you will
never succeed in marketing,

00:16:52.560 --> 00:16:54.960 align:middle line:90%
he didn't have a crystal ball.

00:16:54.960 --> 00:16:56.088 align:middle line:90%
He wasn't a good source.

00:16:56.088 --> 00:16:58.380 align:middle line:84%
There's no way he could be
accurate on that projection.

00:16:58.380 --> 00:17:00.440 align:middle line:84%
I ended up making
literally hundreds

00:17:00.440 --> 00:17:01.440 align:middle line:90%
of millions of dollars--

00:17:01.440 --> 00:17:04.410 align:middle line:84%
and, in fact, billions
of dollars in sales--

00:17:04.410 --> 00:17:05.963 align:middle line:84%
based on my talents
in marketing,

00:17:05.963 --> 00:17:07.380 align:middle line:84%
and he said I would
never succeed.

00:17:07.380 --> 00:17:08.180 align:middle line:90%
So he was wrong.

00:17:08.180 --> 00:17:09.763 align:middle line:84%
Because he didn't
have a crystal ball.

00:17:09.763 --> 00:17:11.910 align:middle line:84%
So first thing you do is,
you consider the source.

00:17:11.910 --> 00:17:14.020 align:middle line:90%
You consider their motivation.

00:17:14.020 --> 00:17:16.200 align:middle line:84%
Now, his motivation was,
he just wanted to hurt me.

00:17:16.200 --> 00:17:18.220 align:middle line:84%
He knew he was going
to fire me, and it

00:17:18.220 --> 00:17:19.470 align:middle line:90%
wasn't good enough to fire me.

00:17:19.470 --> 00:17:20.430 align:middle line:90%
He wanted to hurt me.

00:17:20.430 --> 00:17:23.151 align:middle line:90%


00:17:23.151 --> 00:17:25.109 align:middle line:84%
A lot of times, though,
the motivation is love.

00:17:25.109 --> 00:17:27.569 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes people will criticize
us because they really love us.

00:17:27.569 --> 00:17:28.369 align:middle line:90%
They care about us.

00:17:28.369 --> 00:17:30.497 align:middle line:90%
They want us to succeed.

00:17:30.497 --> 00:17:31.830 align:middle line:90%
But we consider that motivation.

00:17:31.830 --> 00:17:36.120 align:middle line:84%
Now, criticism is like a bucket
of water that's thrown on you.

00:17:36.120 --> 00:17:37.145 align:middle line:90%
It's mainly water.

00:17:37.145 --> 00:17:39.270 align:middle line:84%
Water can't kill you when
it's thrown in your face,

00:17:39.270 --> 00:17:40.633 align:middle line:90%
but it's shocking, it's cold.

00:17:40.633 --> 00:17:43.050 align:middle line:84%
You want to dry it off and get
it off as quick as you can,

00:17:43.050 --> 00:17:44.710 align:middle line:90%
because it's uncomfortable.

00:17:44.710 --> 00:17:47.203 align:middle line:84%
That's the exaggeration
in criticism.

00:17:47.203 --> 00:17:48.870 align:middle line:84%
You're the single
biggest disappointment

00:17:48.870 --> 00:17:50.700 align:middle line:90%
in my entire career.

00:17:50.700 --> 00:17:52.220 align:middle line:90%
That's exaggeration.

00:17:52.220 --> 00:17:53.520 align:middle line:90%
I was only 23 years old.

00:17:53.520 --> 00:17:56.358 align:middle line:84%
He was a huge boss
in this big company.

00:17:56.358 --> 00:17:57.900 align:middle line:84%
There's no way I
could be the biggest

00:17:57.900 --> 00:17:59.395 align:middle line:90%
disappointment in his career.

00:17:59.395 --> 00:18:00.520 align:middle line:90%
So that's the exaggeration.

00:18:00.520 --> 00:18:01.320 align:middle line:90%
That's the water.

00:18:01.320 --> 00:18:03.940 align:middle line:84%
Next we have the sand-- a little
bit of sand in that bucket.

00:18:03.940 --> 00:18:05.533 align:middle line:90%
That's the stinging part.

00:18:05.533 --> 00:18:06.450 align:middle line:90%
That gets in our eyes.

00:18:06.450 --> 00:18:11.880 align:middle line:10%
That's basically the intent
to hurt that sometimes

00:18:11.880 --> 00:18:14.520 align:middle line:10%
goes with the
criticism, or the part

00:18:14.520 --> 00:18:17.005 align:middle line:10%
that just-- if a person
says-- if a husband says,

00:18:17.005 --> 00:18:18.630 align:middle line:10%
you've got to watch
what you're eating.

00:18:18.630 --> 00:18:20.940 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if we should
be having those desserts

00:18:20.940 --> 00:18:21.780 align:middle line:90%
right now.

00:18:21.780 --> 00:18:22.703 align:middle line:90%
That stings.

00:18:22.703 --> 00:18:23.870 align:middle line:90%
Because he's-- it's saying--

00:18:23.870 --> 00:18:24.960 align:middle line:90%
>> He's calling you fat.

00:18:24.960 --> 00:18:25.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:18:25.410 --> 00:18:26.860 align:middle line:90%
I don't like the way you look.

00:18:26.860 --> 00:18:27.100 align:middle line:90%
See?

00:18:27.100 --> 00:18:28.260 align:middle line:90%
And that stings?

00:18:28.260 --> 00:18:29.100 align:middle line:90%
But it's only sand.

00:18:29.100 --> 00:18:30.390 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't kill you.

00:18:30.390 --> 00:18:32.340 align:middle line:90%
Now comes the good part.

00:18:32.340 --> 00:18:34.820 align:middle line:84%
In every bucket of
water of criticism,

00:18:34.820 --> 00:18:38.130 align:middle line:84%
there is anything from a
little tiny flake of gold

00:18:38.130 --> 00:18:40.470 align:middle line:84%
to sometimes giant
golden nuggets.

00:18:40.470 --> 00:18:43.200 align:middle line:84%
So we have to mine that
criticism for gold.

00:18:43.200 --> 00:18:45.822 align:middle line:84%
Now, in the case of my
boss, I thought, OK,

00:18:45.822 --> 00:18:47.280 align:middle line:84%
why does he want
to hurt me so bad?

00:18:47.280 --> 00:18:49.785 align:middle line:84%
Number one, he sensed
disloyalty on my part

00:18:49.785 --> 00:18:50.910 align:middle line:90%
for some things I had done.

00:18:50.910 --> 00:18:52.577 align:middle line:84%
Number two, he sensed
I had never really

00:18:52.577 --> 00:18:54.660 align:middle line:90%
been focused on my job.

00:18:54.660 --> 00:18:57.770 align:middle line:10%
Those were the gold nuggets
I took out of the criticism,

00:18:57.770 --> 00:19:00.340 align:middle line:10%
applied them to the next
job, and did a lot better

00:19:00.340 --> 00:19:01.140 align:middle line:10%
in the next job.

00:19:01.140 --> 00:19:03.750 align:middle line:10%
Because I was more loyal and
I focused on the job better.

00:19:03.750 --> 00:19:05.460 align:middle line:10%
In the case of the
woman who's been told,

00:19:05.460 --> 00:19:08.110 align:middle line:10%
we'd better not eat
desserts, the gold is, hey,

00:19:08.110 --> 00:19:08.910 align:middle line:10%
you know what?

00:19:08.910 --> 00:19:10.600 align:middle line:90%
I know I'm a little overweight.

00:19:10.600 --> 00:19:11.790 align:middle line:90%
I do need to do something.

00:19:11.790 --> 00:19:14.070 align:middle line:84%
I need to start taking it
seriously-- for my health,

00:19:14.070 --> 00:19:16.600 align:middle line:84%
not just because I
want to look better.

00:19:16.600 --> 00:19:19.930 align:middle line:84%
But I do want that too, but
I want to be in better shape.

00:19:19.930 --> 00:19:21.950 align:middle line:84%
So that's a little bit
of the gold we can take.

00:19:21.950 --> 00:19:25.530 align:middle line:84%
And when we focus on the
gold and we convert that gold

00:19:25.530 --> 00:19:28.435 align:middle line:84%
into specific goals,
then all of a sudden

00:19:28.435 --> 00:19:30.060 align:middle line:84%
that criticism becomes
our best friend,

00:19:30.060 --> 00:19:32.580 align:middle line:84%
and becomes a springboard
into achieving something

00:19:32.580 --> 00:19:33.747 align:middle line:90%
we really want to achieve.

00:19:33.747 --> 00:19:34.830 align:middle line:90%
>> So look for the nugget.

00:19:34.830 --> 00:19:36.180 align:middle line:90%
>> Look for the nugget.

00:19:36.180 --> 00:19:38.910 align:middle line:84%
And if you do that exercise on
every criticism you have that

00:19:38.910 --> 00:19:41.680 align:middle line:84%
hurts you, you'll
find those nuggets.

00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:43.650 align:middle line:84%
And then you're no
longer in the sand,

00:19:43.650 --> 00:19:45.960 align:middle line:84%
and the sand doesn't
sting anymore,

00:19:45.960 --> 00:19:48.490 align:middle line:84%
and the water isn't
uncomfortable anymore.

00:19:48.490 --> 00:19:49.290 align:middle line:90%
Those are gone.

00:19:49.290 --> 00:19:52.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Talking about goals here,
I always thought, well,

00:19:52.230 --> 00:19:53.630 align:middle line:90%
you just meditate on your goal.

00:19:53.630 --> 00:19:55.060 align:middle line:90%
You say, no.

00:19:55.060 --> 00:19:56.310 align:middle line:90%
You have got to write it down.

00:19:56.310 --> 00:19:57.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:19:57.110 --> 00:19:58.200 align:middle line:90%
>> Why?

00:19:58.200 --> 00:20:00.075 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, because you
don't really believe it.

00:20:00.075 --> 00:20:03.180 align:middle line:84%
If I said, I want you to
take a trip from Chicago

00:20:03.180 --> 00:20:04.800 align:middle line:90%
to Los Angeles.

00:20:04.800 --> 00:20:08.160 align:middle line:84%
And I say, in fact, I want you
to go to Dick Clark's house.

00:20:08.160 --> 00:20:09.780 align:middle line:90%
He's a good friend of mine.

00:20:09.780 --> 00:20:10.580 align:middle line:90%
And you say, great.

00:20:10.580 --> 00:20:12.038 align:middle line:84%
And I say, hey,
when you get there,

00:20:12.038 --> 00:20:13.860 align:middle line:84%
Dick will hand you a
check for $100,000.

00:20:13.860 --> 00:20:15.390 align:middle line:84%
You've got to be
there in a week--

00:20:15.390 --> 00:20:15.960 align:middle line:90%
or two weeks.

00:20:15.960 --> 00:20:16.920 align:middle line:84%
I'll give you two
weeks to get there.

00:20:16.920 --> 00:20:18.190 align:middle line:90%
And say, great.

00:20:18.190 --> 00:20:20.820 align:middle line:84%
I say, but you can't
have any atlas.

00:20:20.820 --> 00:20:22.120 align:middle line:90%
You can't have a road map.

00:20:22.120 --> 00:20:24.813 align:middle line:84%
You can't have Dick's
street address.

00:20:24.813 --> 00:20:25.980 align:middle line:90%
But you've got to get there.

00:20:25.980 --> 00:20:28.080 align:middle line:84%
And you can't ask
anybody for directions.

00:20:28.080 --> 00:20:29.850 align:middle line:84%
Now, all of a sudden,
hey, it's nice.

00:20:29.850 --> 00:20:31.920 align:middle line:84%
You know he's in
California somewhere,

00:20:31.920 --> 00:20:34.840 align:middle line:84%
but LA alone has 3,500
square miles of houses.

00:20:34.840 --> 00:20:36.090 align:middle line:90%
How are you going to find him?

00:20:36.090 --> 00:20:37.620 align:middle line:84%
How are you even going to
get there in the first place

00:20:37.620 --> 00:20:38.640 align:middle line:90%
without a map?

00:20:38.640 --> 00:20:39.810 align:middle line:90%
With some nice feeling?

00:20:39.810 --> 00:20:42.940 align:middle line:84%
Well, I know it's that way, so
I'll just work my way there.

00:20:42.940 --> 00:20:44.250 align:middle line:90%
It will never happen.

00:20:44.250 --> 00:20:46.920 align:middle line:84%
You've got to have your
destination defined.

00:20:46.920 --> 00:20:50.490 align:middle line:10%
So we teach you a process called
the dream conversion process,

00:20:50.490 --> 00:20:52.200 align:middle line:10%
where you define each
dream in writing.

00:20:52.200 --> 00:20:53.280 align:middle line:90%
And it's not pages.

00:20:53.280 --> 00:20:56.520 align:middle line:84%
It's simply-- a sentence or
a single paragraph will do.

00:20:56.520 --> 00:20:58.510 align:middle line:90%
But you define that in writing.

00:20:58.510 --> 00:21:01.620 align:middle line:84%
And then, when you convert that
dream, through this process,

00:21:01.620 --> 00:21:03.060 align:middle line:90%
into specific goals--

00:21:03.060 --> 00:21:05.630 align:middle line:84%
each goal in the steps,
each step in the tasks,

00:21:05.630 --> 00:21:08.010 align:middle line:84%
and you put a target
date for each task--

00:21:08.010 --> 00:21:11.052 align:middle line:84%
you now have a detailed
roadmap to get to that dream.

00:21:11.052 --> 00:21:13.260 align:middle line:84%
So instead of just being
something that floats around

00:21:13.260 --> 00:21:17.010 align:middle line:84%
up there that you're meditating
on, you have a destination,

00:21:17.010 --> 00:21:19.530 align:middle line:84%
you have a map, you
have a schedule.

00:21:19.530 --> 00:21:21.720 align:middle line:84%
Now you just start to
click off the miles.

00:21:21.720 --> 00:21:24.180 align:middle line:84%
And instead of achieving 1
out of 1,000 dreams that you

00:21:24.180 --> 00:21:27.960 align:middle line:84%
have in your lifetime, you end
up achieving 900 out of 1,000,

00:21:27.960 --> 00:21:29.790 align:middle line:84%
no matter how
impossible they are.

00:21:29.790 --> 00:21:31.298 align:middle line:84%
But that's just
engine number one.

00:21:31.298 --> 00:21:33.090 align:middle line:84%
There are six engines
you've got to ignite.

00:21:33.090 --> 00:21:34.733 align:middle line:84%
But that's a really
important one.

00:21:34.733 --> 00:21:36.150 align:middle line:84%
>> It's an important
one, I think,

00:21:36.150 --> 00:21:41.820 align:middle line:84%
because I think that the
universe gets confused about

00:21:41.820 --> 00:21:44.467 align:middle line:84%
what we want unless
we get very clear.

00:21:44.467 --> 00:21:46.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, one of the
things that I do--

00:21:46.050 --> 00:21:52.290 align:middle line:84%
when I speak to big audiences,
I'll say, what are your dreams?

00:21:52.290 --> 00:21:54.930 align:middle line:84%
And do you know, if I talk to
an audience of 1,000 people,

00:21:54.930 --> 00:21:58.170 align:middle line:90%
I'll get 999 blank looks.

00:21:58.170 --> 00:22:00.630 align:middle line:10%
They all have dreams, but
they haven't defined them.

00:22:00.630 --> 00:22:03.030 align:middle line:84%
If you were to ask me,
what are my dreams?

00:22:03.030 --> 00:22:05.160 align:middle line:84%
I would say, OK, in
which area of my life?

00:22:05.160 --> 00:22:07.230 align:middle line:90%
My relationship with my wife?

00:22:07.230 --> 00:22:09.630 align:middle line:84%
My relationship with
my six children?

00:22:09.630 --> 00:22:10.770 align:middle line:90%
My job?

00:22:10.770 --> 00:22:12.810 align:middle line:90%
Particular projects on my job?

00:22:12.810 --> 00:22:15.600 align:middle line:84%
Because I have my dreams
defined in all of those areas.

00:22:15.600 --> 00:22:18.570 align:middle line:84%
>> The nice thing about
your book is that it's not--

00:22:18.570 --> 00:22:20.520 align:middle line:84%
when you talk about
successful people here,

00:22:20.520 --> 00:22:22.600 align:middle line:84%
you're not talking
about business only.

00:22:22.600 --> 00:22:23.400 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:22:23.400 --> 00:22:26.310 align:middle line:84%
>> You're saying, define
your dreams in every area

00:22:26.310 --> 00:22:28.180 align:middle line:84%
of your life, and then
you can have them.

00:22:28.180 --> 00:22:28.980 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:22:28.980 --> 00:22:31.200 align:middle line:10%
For me, my most important
areas in life-- number one

00:22:31.200 --> 00:22:32.310 align:middle line:10%
is my relationship with God.

00:22:32.310 --> 00:22:33.977 align:middle line:10%
Number two is my
relationship with wife.

00:22:33.977 --> 00:22:36.910 align:middle line:10%
Business is number four, even
though it's important to me.

00:22:36.910 --> 00:22:39.750 align:middle line:84%
So if I succeed in my
dreams in my business

00:22:39.750 --> 00:22:43.180 align:middle line:84%
and I fail in those first two
areas, then I fail in life.

00:22:43.180 --> 00:22:44.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we've had a
wonderful time here.

